35static const int EXPECTED_CORNER_BITS[] = {
36 0xee0, // 07340 XXX .XX X.. ...
37 0x1dc, // 00734 ... XXX .XX X..
38 0x83b, // 04073 X.. ... XXX .XX
39 0x707, // 03407 .XX X.. ... XXX
40};
41
42// return -1 in case of error
43static int GetRotation(const std::array<int, 4>& sides, int length)
44{
45 // In a normal pattern, we expect to See
46 // ** .* D A
47 // * *
48 //
49 // . *
50 // .. .. C B
51 //
52 // Grab the 3 bits from each of the sides the form the locator pattern and concatenate
53 // into a 12-bit integer. Start with the bit at A
54 int cornerBits = 0;
55 for (int side : sides) {
56 // XX......X where X's are orientation marks
57 int t = ((side >> (length - 2)) << 1) + (side & 1);
58 cornerBits = (cornerBits << 3) + t;
59 }
60 // Mov the bottom bit to the top, so that the three bits of the locator pattern at A are
61 // together. cornerBits is now:
62 // 3 orientation bits at A || 3 orientation bits at B || ... || 3 orientation bits at D
63 cornerBits = ((cornerBits & 1) << 11) + (cornerBits >> 1);
64 // The result shift indicates which element of BullsEyeCorners[] goes into the top-left
65 // corner. Since the four rotation values have a Hamming distance of 8, we
66 // can easily tolerate two errors.
67 for (int shift = 0; shift < 4; shift++) {
68 if (BitHacks::CountBitsSet(cornerBits ^ EXPECTED_CORNER_BITS[shift]) <= 2) {
69 return shift;
70 }
71 }
72 return -1;
73}

75inline static bool IsValidPoint(int x, int y, int imgWidth, int imgHeight)
76{
77 return x >= 0 && x < imgWidth && y > 0 && y < imgHeight;
78}
79
80inline static bool IsValidPoint(const ResultPoint& point, int imgWidth, int imgHeight)
81{
82 return IsValidPoint(RoundToNearest(point.x()), RoundToNearest(point.y()), imgWidth, imgHeight);
83}
84
85/**
86* Samples a line.
87*
88* @param p1 start point (inclusive)
89* @param p2 end point (exclusive)
90* @param size number of bits
91* @return the array of bits as an int (first bit is high-order bit of result)
92*/
93static int SampleLine(const BitMatrix& image, const ResultPoint& p1, const ResultPoint& p2, int size)
94{
95 int result = 0;
96
97 float d = distance(p1, p2);
98 float moduleSize = d / size;
99 float px = p1.x();
100 float py = p1.y();
101 float dx = moduleSize * (p2.x() - p1.x()) / d;
102 float dy = moduleSize * (p2.y() - p1.y()) / d;
103 for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
104 if (image.get(RoundToNearest(px + i * dx), RoundToNearest(py + i * dy))) {
105 result |= 1 << (size - i - 1);
106 }
107 }
108 return result;
109}

111/**
112* Corrects the parameter bits using Reed-Solomon algorithm.
113*
114* @param parameterData parameter bits
115* @param compact true if this is a compact Aztec code
116*/
117static bool GetCorrectedParameterData(int64_t parameterData, bool compact, int& result)
118{
119 int numCodewords;
120 int numDataCodewords;
121
122 if (compact) {
123 numCodewords = 7;
124 numDataCodewords = 2;
125 }
126 else {
127 numCodewords = 10;
128 numDataCodewords = 4;
129 }
130
131 int numECCodewords = numCodewords - numDataCodewords;
132 std::vector<int> parameterWords(numCodewords);
133 for (int i = numCodewords - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
134 parameterWords[i] = (int)parameterData & 0xF;
135 parameterData >>= 4;
136 }
137 if (!ReedSolomonDecoder::Decode(GenericGF::AztecParam(), parameterWords, numECCodewords))
138 return false;
139
140 // Toss the error correction. Just return the data as an integer
141 result = 0;
142 for (int i = 0; i < numDataCodewords; i++) {
143 result = (result << 4) + parameterWords[i];
144 }
145 return true;
146}

148/**
149* Extracts the number of data layers and data blocks from the layer around the bull's eye.
150*
151* @param bullsEyeCorners the array of bull's eye corners
152* @throws NotFoundException in case of too many errors or invalid parameters
153*/
154static bool ExtractParameters(const BitMatrix& image, const std::array<ResultPoint, 4>& bullsEyeCorners, bool compact, int nbCenterLayers, int& nbLayers, int& nbDataBlocks, int& shift)
155{
156 if (!IsValidPoint(bullsEyeCorners[0], image.width(), image.height()) || !IsValidPoint(bullsEyeCorners[1], image.width(), image.height()) ||
157 !IsValidPoint(bullsEyeCorners[2], image.width(), image.height()) || !IsValidPoint(bullsEyeCorners[3], image.width(), image.height())) {
158 return false;
159 }
160 int length = 2 * nbCenterLayers;
161 // Get the bits around the bull's eye
162 std::array<int, 4> sides = {
163 SampleLine(image, bullsEyeCorners[0], bullsEyeCorners[1], length), // Right side
164 SampleLine(image, bullsEyeCorners[1], bullsEyeCorners[2], length), // Bottom
165 SampleLine(image, bullsEyeCorners[2], bullsEyeCorners[3], length), // Left side
166 SampleLine(image, bullsEyeCorners[3], bullsEyeCorners[0], length) // Top
167 };
168
169 // bullsEyeCorners[shift] is the corner of the bulls'eye that has three
170 // orientation marks.
171 // sides[shift] is the row/column that goes from the corner with three
172 // orientation marks to the corner with two.
173 shift = GetRotation(sides, length);
174 if (shift < 0) {
175 return false;
176 }
177
178 // Flatten the parameter bits into a single 28- or 40-bit long
179 int64_t parameterData = 0;
180 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
181 int side = sides[(shift + i) % 4];
182 if (compact) {
183 // Each side of the form ..XXXXXXX. where Xs are parameter data
184 parameterData <<= 7;
185 parameterData += (side >> 1) & 0x7F;
186 }
187 else {
188 // Each side of the form ..XXXXX.XXXXX. where Xs are parameter data
189 parameterData <<= 10;
190 parameterData += ((side >> 2) & (0x1f << 5)) + ((side >> 1) & 0x1F);
191 }
192 }
193
194 // Corrects parameter data using RS. Returns just the data portion
195 // without the error correction.
196 int correctedData;
197 if (!GetCorrectedParameterData(parameterData, compact, correctedData)) {
198 return false;
199 }
200
201 if (compact) {
202 // 8 bits: 2 bits layers and 6 bits data blocks
203 nbLayers = (correctedData >> 6) + 1;
204 nbDataBlocks = (correctedData & 0x3F) + 1;
205 }
206 else {
207 // 16 bits: 5 bits layers and 11 bits data blocks
208 nbLayers = (correctedData >> 11) + 1;
209 nbDataBlocks = (correctedData & 0x7FF) + 1;
210 }
211 return true;
212}

215/**
216* Gets the color of a segment
217*
218* @return 1 if segment more than 90% black, -1 if segment is more than 90% white, 0 else
219*/
220static int GetColor(const BitMatrix& image, const PointI& p1, const PointI& p2)
221{
222 if (!IsValidPoint(p1.x, p1.y, image.width(), image.height()) ||
223 !IsValidPoint(p2.x, p2.y, image.width(), image.height()))
224 return 0;
225
226 float d = distance(p1, p2);
227 float dx = (p2.x - p1.x) / d;
228 float dy = (p2.y - p1.y) / d;
229 int error = 0;
230
231 float px = static_cast<float>(p1.x);
232 float py = static_cast<float>(p1.y);
233
234 bool colorModel = image.get(p1.x, p1.y);
235 int iMax = (int)std::ceil(d);
236 for (int i = 0; i < iMax; i++) {
237 px += dx;
238 py += dy;
239 if (image.get(RoundToNearest(px), RoundToNearest(py)) != colorModel) {
240 error++;
241 }
242 }
243
244 float errRatio = error / d;
245
246 if (errRatio > 0.1f && errRatio < 0.9f) {
247 return 0;
248 }
249
250 return (errRatio <= 0.1f) == colorModel ? 1 : -1;
251}
252
253/**
254* @return true if the border of the rectangle passed in parameter is compound of white points only
255* or black points only
256*/
257static bool IsWhiteOrBlackRectangle(const BitMatrix& image, const PointI& pt1, const PointI& pt2, const PointI& pt3, const PointI& pt4) {
258
259 int corr = 3;
260
261 PointI p1{ pt1.x - corr, pt1.y + corr };
262 PointI p2{ pt2.x - corr, pt2.y - corr };
263 PointI p3{ pt3.x + corr, pt3.y - corr };
264 PointI p4{ pt4.x + corr, pt4.y + corr };
265
266 int cInit = GetColor(image, p4, p1);
267
268 if (cInit == 0) {
269 return false;
270 }
271
272 int c = GetColor(image, p1, p2);
273
274 if (c != cInit) {
275 return false;
276 }
277
278 c = GetColor(image, p2, p3);
279
280 if (c != cInit) {
281 return false;
282 }
283
284 c = GetColor(image, p3, p4);
285
286 return c == cInit;
287
288}
289
290/**
291* Gets the coordinate of the first point with a different color in the given direction
292*/
293static PointI GetFirstDifferent(const BitMatrix& image, const PointI& init, bool color, int dx, int dy) {
294 int x = init.x + dx;
295 int y = init.y + dy;
296
297 while (IsValidPoint(x, y, image.width(), image.height()) && image.get(x, y) == color) {
298 x += dx;
299 y += dy;
300 }
301
302 x -= dx;
303 y -= dy;
304
305 while (IsValidPoint(x, y, image.width(), image.height()) && image.get(x, y) == color) {
306 x += dx;
307 }
308 x -= dx;
309
310 while (IsValidPoint(x, y, image.width(), image.height()) && image.get(x, y) == color) {
311 y += dy;
312 }
313 y -= dy;
314
315 return PointI{ x, y };
316}

318/**
319* Expand the square represented by the corner points by pushing out equally in all directions
320*
321* @param cornerPoints the corners of the square, which has the bull's eye at its center
322* @param oldSide the original length of the side of the square in the target bit matrix
323* @param newSide the new length of the size of the square in the target bit matrix
324* @return the corners of the expanded square
325*/
326static void ExpandSquare(std::array<ResultPoint, 4>& cornerPoints, float oldSide, float newSide)
327{
328 float ratio = newSide / (2 * oldSide);
329 float dx = cornerPoints[0].x() - cornerPoints[2].x();
330 float dy = cornerPoints[0].y() - cornerPoints[2].y();
331 float centerx = (cornerPoints[0].x() + cornerPoints[2].x()) / 2.0f;
332 float centery = (cornerPoints[0].y() + cornerPoints[2].y()) / 2.0f;
333
334 cornerPoints[0] = ResultPoint(centerx + ratio * dx, centery + ratio * dy);
335 cornerPoints[2] = ResultPoint(centerx - ratio * dx, centery - ratio * dy);
336
337 dx = cornerPoints[1].x() - cornerPoints[3].x();
338 dy = cornerPoints[1].y() - cornerPoints[3].y();
339 centerx = (cornerPoints[1].x() + cornerPoints[3].x()) / 2.0f;
340 centery = (cornerPoints[1].y() + cornerPoints[3].y()) / 2.0f;
341 cornerPoints[1] = ResultPoint(centerx + ratio * dx, centery + ratio * dy);
342 cornerPoints[3] = ResultPoint(centerx - ratio * dx, centery - ratio * dy);
343}

346/**
347* Finds the corners of a bull-eye centered on the passed point.
348* This returns the centers of the diagonal points just outside the bull's eye
349* Returns [topRight, bottomRight, bottomLeft, topLeft]
350*
351* @param pCenter Center point
352* @return The corners of the bull-eye
353* @throws NotFoundException If no valid bull-eye can be found
354*/
355static bool GetBullsEyeCorners(const BitMatrix& image, const PointI& pCenter, std::array<ResultPoint, 4>& result, bool& compact, int& nbCenterLayers)
356{
357 PointI pina = pCenter;
358 PointI pinb = pCenter;
359 PointI pinc = pCenter;
360 PointI pind = pCenter;
361
362 bool color = true;
363 for (nbCenterLayers = 1; nbCenterLayers < 9; nbCenterLayers++) {
364 PointI pouta = GetFirstDifferent(image, pina, color, 1, -1);
365 PointI poutb = GetFirstDifferent(image, pinb, color, 1, 1);
366 PointI poutc = GetFirstDifferent(image, pinc, color, -1, 1);
367 PointI poutd = GetFirstDifferent(image, pind, color, -1, -1);
368
369 //d a
370 //
371 //c b
372
373 if (nbCenterLayers > 2) {
374 float q = distance(poutd, pouta) * nbCenterLayers / (distance(pind, pina) * (nbCenterLayers + 2));
375 if (q < 0.75 || q > 1.25 || !IsWhiteOrBlackRectangle(image, pouta, poutb, poutc, poutd)) {
376 break;
377 }
378 }
379
380 pina = pouta;
381 pinb = poutb;
382 pinc = poutc;
383 pind = poutd;
384
385 color = !color;
386 }
387
388 if (nbCenterLayers != 5 && nbCenterLayers != 7) {
389 return false;
390 }
391
392 compact = nbCenterLayers == 5;
393
394 // Expand the square by .5 pixel in each direction so that we're on the border
395 // between the white square and the black square
396 result[0] = ResultPoint(pina.x + 0.5f, pina.y - 0.5f);
397 result[1] = ResultPoint(pinb.x + 0.5f, pinb.y + 0.5f);
398 result[2] = ResultPoint(pinc.x - 0.5f, pinc.y + 0.5f);
399 result[3] = ResultPoint(pind.x - 0.5f, pind.y - 0.5f);
400
401 // Expand the square so that its corners are the centers of the points
402 // just outside the bull's eye.
403 ExpandSquare(result, static_cast<float>(2 * nbCenterLayers - 3), static_cast<float>(2 * nbCenterLayers));
404 return true;
405}

407/**
408* Finds a candidate center point of an Aztec code from an image
409*
410* @return the center point
411*/
412static PointI GetMatrixCenter(const BitMatrix& image)
413{
414 //Get a white rectangle that can be the border of the matrix in center bull's eye or
415 ResultPoint pointA, pointB, pointC, pointD;
416 if (!WhiteRectDetector::Detect(image, pointA, pointB, pointC, pointD)) {
417 // This exception can be in case the initial rectangle is white
418 // In that case, surely in the bull's eye, we try to expand the rectangle.
419 int cx = image.width() / 2;
420 int cy = image.height() / 2;
421 pointA = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx + 7, cy - 7 }, false, 1, -1);
422 pointB = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx + 7, cy + 7 }, false, 1, 1);
423 pointC = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx - 7, cy + 7 }, false, -1, 1);
424 pointD = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx - 7, cy - 7 }, false, -1, -1);
425 }
426
427 //Compute the center of the rectangle
428 int cx = RoundToNearest((pointA.x() + pointD.x() + pointB.x() + pointC.x()) / 4.0f);
429 int cy = RoundToNearest((pointA.y() + pointD.y() + pointB.y() + pointC.y()) / 4.0f);
430
431 // Redetermine the white rectangle starting from previously computed center.
432 // This will ensure that we end up with a white rectangle in center bull's eye
433 // in order to compute a more accurate center.
434 if (!WhiteRectDetector::Detect(image, 15, cx, cy, pointA, pointB, pointC, pointD)) {
435 // This exception can be in case the initial rectangle is white
436 // In that case we try to expand the rectangle.
437 pointA = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx + 7, cy - 7 }, false, 1, -1);
438 pointB = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx + 7, cy + 7 }, false, 1, 1);
439 pointC = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx - 7, cy + 7 }, false, -1, 1);
440 pointD = GetFirstDifferent(image, { cx - 7, cy - 7 }, false, -1, -1);
441 }
442
443 // Recompute the center of the rectangle
444 cx = RoundToNearest((pointA.x() + pointD.x() + pointB.x() + pointC.x()) / 4.0f);
445 cy = RoundToNearest((pointA.y() + pointD.y() + pointB.y() + pointC.y()) / 4.0f);
446
447 return{ cx, cy };
448}
449
450static int GetDimension(bool compact, int nbLayers)
451{
452 if (compact) {
453 return 4 * nbLayers + 11;
454 }
455 if (nbLayers <= 4) {
456 return 4 * nbLayers + 15;
457 }
458 return 4 * nbLayers + 2 * ((nbLayers - 4) / 8 + 1) + 15;
459}

461/**
462* Creates a BitMatrix by sampling the provided image.
463* topLeft, topRight, bottomRight, and bottomLeft are the centers of the squares on the
464* diagonal just outside the bull's eye.
465*/
466static ZXing::DetectorResult SampleGrid(const BitMatrix& image, const ResultPoint& topLeft, const ResultPoint& topRight, const ResultPoint& bottomRight, const ResultPoint& bottomLeft, bool compact, int nbLayers, int nbCenterLayers)
467{
468 int dimension = GetDimension(compact, nbLayers);
469
470 float low = dimension / 2.0f - nbCenterLayers;
471 float high = dimension / 2.0f + nbCenterLayers;
472
473 return SampleGrid(image, dimension, dimension,
474 PerspectiveTransform{{PointF{low, low}, {high, low}, {high, high}, {low, high}},
475 {topLeft, topRight, bottomRight, bottomLeft}});
476}
477
478DetectorResult Detector::Detect(const BitMatrix& image, bool isMirror)
479{
480 // 1. Get the center of the aztec matrix
481 auto pCenter = GetMatrixCenter(image);
482
483 // 2. Get the center points of the four diagonal points just outside the bull's eye
484 // [topRight, bottomRight, bottomLeft, topLeft]
485 std::array<ResultPoint, 4> bullsEyeCorners;
486 bool compact = false;
487 int nbCenterLayers = 0;
488 if (!GetBullsEyeCorners(image, pCenter, bullsEyeCorners, compact, nbCenterLayers)) {
489 return {};
490 }
491
492 if (isMirror) {
493 std::swap(bullsEyeCorners[0], bullsEyeCorners[2]);
494 }
495
496 // 3. Get the size of the matrix and other parameters from the bull's eye
497 int nbLayers = 0;
498 int nbDataBlocks = 0;
499 int shift = 0;
500 if (!ExtractParameters(image, bullsEyeCorners, compact, nbCenterLayers, nbLayers, nbDataBlocks, shift)) {
501 return {};
502 }
503
504 // 4. Sample the grid
505 return {SampleGrid(image, bullsEyeCorners[(shift + 0) % 4], bullsEyeCorners[(shift + 1) % 4],
506 bullsEyeCorners[(shift + 2) % 4], bullsEyeCorners[(shift + 3) % 4], compact, nbLayers,
507 nbCenterLayers),
508 compact, nbDataBlocks, nbLayers};
509}
